main event: An unidentified object was observed in the Pacific Ocean in 1964, but insufficient information was available to identify it.
interesting points: The report from Project Blue Book includes a detailed analysis from Dr. Hynek,The sighting took place in the Pacific Ocean at the coordinates 45-00N 172-30W,No physical evidence or photographs were documented in the report,The nature of the object remains unknown, and it was suggested that it could potentially be a satellite.
